1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
SAI Rolotech Smart Engines —
a near COPRA-class roll-forming engineering platform.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Designed for precision. Built for production.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Start by selecting your material —
Galvanised Steel DX51D —
and defining the section profile.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:24,000
A lipped channel, 2 millimetre thick,
120 millimetres wide.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Load a saved project or enter parameters directly.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,000
The station engine calculates 13 forming passes,
distributing bend angle incrementally across each station.

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Watch the flower progression unfold —
each pass bringing the flat strip closer to the final profile.

8
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Roll contour is generated automatically —
upper and lower rolls matched to the strip geometry.

9
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Springback correction applied per pass.
Force, power and torque calculated at each station.

10
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Bend allowance and flat blank width — calculated instantly.

11
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Bill of Materials generated with shaft,
bearing and roll specifications.

12
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Process card ready for the shop floor.

13
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Tooling library saves your roll sets for reuse.

14
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Export to DXF, STEP, or a full CAD pack — one click.

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Advanced Process Simulation Precheck —
pass-by-pass stress, strain and contact analysis.

16
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Defect probability, fracture risk, wrinkling
and edge wave flags — all instant.

17
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,000
FEA-ready solver decks generated
for CalculiX and Abaqus when you need full simulation.

18
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,000
720 automated tests. 29 engine modules.
45 live API endpoints.

19
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,000
SAI Rolotech Smart Engines —
engineering-grade precision, from input to export.
